The paper primarily focuses on the social and criminal aspects of cybercrime, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the platforms and dynamics of online groups, which could also place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also touches on the motives and actions of cybercriminal groups, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
